<div id="entry-53">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="../entry.php_a_2009_10_dr-tahar-featured-in-oiq-publication.php">Dr. Tahar featured in OIQ publication</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2009-10-31T17:57:18-05:00">Saturday Oct 31, 2009
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			<b>Dr. Sofiene Tahar</b> was recently interviewed by the <a class="zem_slink" href="http://www.oiq.qc.ca/" title="Ordre des ingénieurs du Québec" rel="homepage">Ordre des Ingenieurs du Quebec</a> on his research activities on "Verification." A summary of the interview has been just released in the OIQ premier magazine, PLAN, as part of a report on security.<br /><br />Dr. Tahar joined the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering of <a class="zem_slink" href="http://www.concordia.ca/" title="Concordia University" rel="homepage">Concordia University</a> in 1996 as an Assistant Professor. He was promoted to Associate Professor in 2000 and to Professor in 2006. In 2007, he was apointed Tier 1 (senior) Concordia University Research Chair (equivalent to <a class="zem_slink" href="http://www.chairs.gc.ca/" title="Canada Research Chair" rel="homepage">CRC</a> Tier 1) in Formal Verification of System-on-Chip<br /><br />PLAN Magazine is magazine is widely distributed to all OIQ members.<br /><br /><a href="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/tahar.jpg"><img alt="Sofiene Tahar" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/assets_c/2010/01/tahar-thumb-440x393-73.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="margin: 0pt auto 20px; text-align: center; display: block;" width="440" height="393" /></a><br />


		</div>
	
	</div>
</div>
<div class="clear">&nbsp;</div>



    

    <div id="entry-42">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="../entry.php_a_2009_10_ece-prof-wins-best-paper-award.php">ECE Prof wins Best Paper Award</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2009-10-17T17:09:59-05:00">Saturday Oct 17, 2009
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			<b>Dr. Shah Jahinuzzaman</b>, assistant professor at Electrical and Computer Engineering, won the best paper award for the "Soft Error Robust Impulse and TSPC Flip-flops in 90nm CMOS" paper/presentation at the Microsystems and Nanoelectronics Research Conference (MNRC) in Ottawa on October 14, 2009. The award includes the Gold Leaf Certificate and a $1000 cheque.<br /><br /> 
		</div>
	
	</div>
</div>
<div class="clear">&nbsp;</div>



    

    <div id="entry-41">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="../entry.php_a_2009_10_presidents-conference-on-surveilance-security-the-end-of-privacy.php">President's Conference on Surveilance, Security & the end of Privacy</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2009-10-15T17:07:19-05:00">Thursday Oct 15, 2009
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			On Wednesday, November 4, Concordia University will be hosting a day of discovery with a new edition of the President's Conference Series. ENCS's own <b>Ching Suen </b>(Concordia Chair in AI &amp; Pattern Recognition and Director of the Centre for Pattern Recognition and Machine Intelligence) and <b>Mourad Debbabi</b> (professor and Director of the Concordia Institute for Information Systems Engineering) will speak at the event: see below for details.<br /><br />Visit <a href="http://www.concordia.ca/presidentsconferences">www.concordia.ca/presidentsconferences</a> for more information.<br />
		</div>
	
	</div>
</div>
